<HEAD>Soviet Emigree Accused Of Being Moscow Spy Goes On Trial</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEL AVIV, Israel (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Soviet emigrant with links to <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> politicians and military officers went on trial Monday insisting his confession of spying for the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> was obtained under duress, his lawyer said. <PERSON> Shabtai </PERSON> <PERSON> Kalmanovich </PERSON>, 43, was taken into the closed courtroom under heavy guard. He stopped briefly to embrace his father and wife who handed him newspapers, cigarettes and a sack of cheese and lettuce sandwichs. Attorney <PERSON> Amnon </PERSON> <PERSON> Zichroni </PERSON> said his client took extensive notes during the five-hour hearing. He said only one witness testified Monday, an agent of <PERSON> Shin </PERSON> <PERSON> Bet </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s secret service, who helped obtain <PERSON> Kalmanovich </PERSON>'s confession during his eight months in custody. `` We are arguing that this confession was not made voluntarily,'' <PERSON> Zichroni </PERSON> told The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>. `` I am not permitted ... to give details, but I can say we oppose its submission.'' The exact charges <PERSON> Kalmanovich </PERSON> faces have not been revealed. He is expected to plead innocent after the hearing resumes Thursday. <PERSON> Kalmanovich </PERSON>, who emigrated from the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> in 1971, was arrested in December. He had established himself in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> as an international businessman, an activist in the <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> and a socialite who mixed with leading politicians and senior army officers. <PERSON> Zichroni </PERSON> declined to comment on foreign reports that the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> may be working on a deal to trade <PERSON> Kalmanovich </PERSON> in a spy swap involving <PERSON> Jonathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Jay </PERSON> <PE