<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Heavyweight boxing champion <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> is recuperating today from minor head and chest injuries after apparently being knocked out in a single-car accident near his upstate training camp. <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> BMW </ORGANIZATION> apparently skidded on a wet road Sunday morning, said a spokesman for the boxer, <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Klores </PERSON>, who gave no other details of the crash. A witness said the accident occurred while <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> was driving his car out of the yard at his adopted family's home in <LOCATION> Catskill </LOCATION> and it skidded and slammed into a tree. He was found, apparently unconscious. `` <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> was just leaning back in his car seat and I took his pulse,'' said <PERSON> Yvonne </PERSON> <PERSON> Conrad </PERSON>, a niece of <PERSON> Camille </PERSON> <PERSON> Ewald </PERSON>, whom <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> has been close to since he began training in <LOCATION> Catskill </LOCATION> eight years ago. `` He was normal, his breathing was n't heavy or labored. I did n't hear anything wrong with him We just could n't arouse him. We tried to wake him up by asking ` <PERSON> Mike </PERSON>, <PERSON> Mike </PERSON>,' and we just could n't get anything from him.'' <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON>, who was recovering from a broken bone in his right hand suffered in a street fight two weeks ago with heavyweight <PERSON> Mitch </PERSON> <PERSON> Green </PERSON>, was taken to two upstate hospitals before being transferred Sunday night to <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Presbyterian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> here. <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> was hospitalized for observation and diagnostic tests, said Dr. <PERSON> Carolyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Britton </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Presbyterian </LOCATION>. `` He suffered minor trauma to the head and the chest wall,'' <PERSON> Britton </PERSON> said, adding that <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON>'s condition was stable. `` He's neurologicallly normal.'' As <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> arrived in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, his wife, actress <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Givens </PERSON>, tried to keep waiting photographers away from her husband. As cameramen pressed forward, <PERSON> Givens </PERSON> pushed them back, shouting, `` Give him a break.'' <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON>, whose championship bout against British champ <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Bruno </PERSON> was recently postponed until Oct. 22 because of the hand injury, was scheduled to accompany his wife to the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> on Wednesday. In his last fight in the ring on June 27, <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> knocked out previously unbeaten <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Spinks </PERSON> in 91 seconds, earning $ 22 million.
