ION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> to gain worldwide stature and exposure. Several times in recent years, shooting has occurred across the tense Demilitarized Zone that divides the two countries. And in November, a <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> jetliner disappeared near <LOCATION> Burma </LOCATION>, with all 115 people aboard believed to have died. A self-described North Korean agent said she helped plant a bomb aboard the plane to disrupt <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>'s presidential elections and the Olympics. `` As for ` terrorism,' it is utterly alien to us and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> itself is the chieftain of state terrorism as already exposed to the world,'' the nNorth's <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> statement said. `` We have no intention to ` invade the South' and this is fully borne out by the historical facts over the last 35 years'' since the Korean War cease-fire, the statement said. It also accused <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> of creating tension on the troubled <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> peninsula through various military exercises as an excuse to invade <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>. `` They are abusing the name of Olympics for stepping up the preparations for a war of aggression against our republic and plainly shows their scheme to cause a shocking incident and start another war in <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> in case the Games do not go as they wish,'' the statement said. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> maintains about 42,000 troops in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> and is planning to hold naval exercises off the <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> peninsula </LOCATION> during the Games to deter any attacks from outs