y intend to reduce their numbers, which total more than 60 warships of various types, if the Iran-Iraq cease-fire continues to hold. <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>, the first to cut back, withdrew a frigate the day after the truce began. It still has five ships _ two frigates, two mine-hunters and a supply vessel _ in the gulf region. Other warships include eight British, one Belgian, one Dutch and as many as nine Soviet vessels.
