he station and convince advertisers that Jews will watch its programs. <PERSON> Vlock </PERSON> and his mother, <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> <PERSON> Vlock </PERSON>, chairwoman of <LOCATION> Bridgeways </LOCATION>, are confident that cable networks will make room for Channel 43. `` People are very concerned about their roots. It's a trend in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> in all ethnicities today,'' <PERSON> Laurel </PERSON> <PERSON> Vlock </PERSON> said. Said <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Vlock </PERSON>: `` We offer a large, focused, loyal and well-educated audience ... what more does an advertiser want.''
