e and is proud of his service in the National Guard. Thirty-nine percent of those polled said they regarded <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s choice of <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> as a `` negative,'' 31 percent said it was `` positive,'' and the rest had no opinion Six percent of those surveyed were Vietnam-era veterans. Among them, the choice of <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> was viewed as positive by 22 percent and negative by 49 percent. The poll indicated that <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> vice presidential nominee <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> was viewed positively by 41 percent of all respondents, and negatively by 23 percent. The margin of error for questions asked all respondents was 3.5 percentage points, and 6 points for the Vietnam-era veterans.
