indicted <PERSON> Hamadi </PERSON> on air piracy and murder charges, but <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> has refused an extradition request from <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. In April, a <LOCATION> Duesseldorf </LOCATION> court sentenced one of his brothers, <PERSON> Abbas </PERSON> <PERSON> Hamadi </PERSON>, to 13 years in prison for kidnapping two German businessmen in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> in an unsuccesful bid to force <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> to free <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> from prison. The other three men involved in the <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> hijacking remain at large.
