<HEAD>Prices Discussed at Cocoa Producer-Consumer Talks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The 37-nation International Cocoa Organization Monday began discussing differences over the support price for cocoa on the first day of crucial talks on the body's future, delegates said. The `` logical consequence of non-agreement'' will be to consider implementing plans to start winding down the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION>, said West German chief delegate <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Baron </PERSON>. These plans, officially unveiled Monday, call for halting on Oct. 1 the current levy on internationally traded cocoa _ the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION>'s main source of finance _ as well as for the selling off of the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION>'s stockpiles to meet running costs during the coming year. Delegates said ending the levy would acknowledge that the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> had no further role to play in supporting prices. Already the body lacks enough money to implement a possible new stockpiling scheme because some producers are behind in payments to the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION>, delegates said. The <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> is owed a total of $ 70 million, they said. Prices on world markets last week reached their lowest levels in seven years, reflecting a current world cocoa glut and an absence of <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> support operations since February, when intervention buying was indefinitely suspended. The proposed new stockpiling scheme, under which producers would receive <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> financing to hold back up to 120,000 metric tons of cocoa from the market, has been blocked by lack of funds and the dispute between producers and consumers over the support price for cocoa. Consumers say under the provisions of the price pact administered by the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> a cut in the price was automatically triggered in March, but this interpretation is rejected by the producers. A special panel set up to resolve the dispute reported to the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> today that it was split 3 to 2 on the issue. Its independent Belgian chairman, <PERSON> Jean </PERSON> <PERSON> Parotte </PERSON>, backed the view of the panel's two consumer members while two producer representatives backed their side's view, delegates said. It is now up to the full <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION> to decide the matter and delegates said the continued polarization of views made a solution appear very difficult to attain. <PERSON> Baron </PERSON> said even if agreement were possible, consumers would then press for a further cut in the support price to reflect recent developments on the market. Even then the new stockpiling scheme could not operate without payment of producer debts to the <ORGANIZATION> ICCO </ORGANIZATION>, consumer delegates said. `` The withholding scheme is linked to the arrears,'' said <PERSON> Baron </PERSON>.
</TEXT>
